AGI - The fire budget hit a residential building in Istanbul has risen to 29 dead. It is reported by Governor Davut Gul. The wounded are three. "An investigation is underway," the authorities added. The fire would have burst into the basement of a 16-story building in Gayrettepe, in the central district of Besiktas.
&nbsp;
The newly elected mayor of Istanbul, <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-02/fire-istanbul-morti-e-feriti-25894047/">Ekrem Imamoglu</a>, noticed in the basement there was a disco. On the spot, rescue operations are carried out with numerous fire teams engaged to extract the people trapped. The Istanbul Prefect commissioned two magistrates and stated that six people are under arrest: Contrary to what was assumed, in fact, the fire would start from a playroom where maintenance and renovation work was underway, located on the ground floor of the adjacent building the palace then wrapped by the fire.&nbsp;
