&nbsp;
"Call some facts on the case of Ilaria Salis> - write Viktor Orban's spokesman on social - from mid-February, Ilaria Salis' father, <a href="https://www.agi.it/cronaca/news/2024-03-30/caso-salis-mattarella-padre-ilaria-grande-vicinanza-25864104/" For this reason they asked for house arrests in Italy, concerning which Szijjarto (the Hungarian Foreign Minister n.d.r.) said that "it will be decided by the court, which is an independent body". Last Thursday, the Budapest court rejected Salis' request for house arrest, stating that there was a risk that he would flee or hide. For you, the D.A. now calls for an 11-year sentence. Why? Because there is reasonable suspicion that Ilaria Salis went to Hungary with its two anti-fascist members with the aim of beating innocent people on the streets of Budapest. Meanwhile, the Italian media did their best to paint Salis as a martyr," adds Kovacs.
&nbsp;
"It is surprising that they are trying to interfere in a Hungarian judiciary case from Italy," Szijjarto said about a month ago. Emphasizing the premeditated nature of the act, the minister said that "it was not a crime committed by whim but a well-thought and planned act. They almost killed people in Hungary, and now she's painted like a martyr." &nbsp;

